  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Bolstering Ethical Recruitment Policies and Practice to Enhance Safe and Orderly Labour Migration Pathways, Prevent Exploitation and Better Protect Migrant Workers from Uganda</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project addresses safe and transparent labour migration practices through ethical recruitment and protection of migrant workers&apos;; women, girls, men and boys, human social and economic and labour rights. The project will be implemented in close collaboration with the Ministry of Gender Labour and Socal Development, the district local authorities and UAERA, which IOM already has established strong relationships with. It will also benefit from the technical guidance of the IRIS Secretariat. The project plans to implement a holistic ethical recruitment intervention that is tailor-made for Uganda. Bringing in global learning of ethical recruitment and IRIS implementation the project reflects the priorities of the Regional Ministerial Forum on Migration (RMFM) on harmonisation of labour migration policies in East and Horn of Africa, A United Approach on Safe, Regular and Human Labour Migration (Communique and Call to Action Priorities 2020-2023). A similar project has been funded in Kenya and the 2 projects will be moving in parallel.</narrative>
  </description>
